The province is recovering from recent floods that claimed the lives of 4 hundred and 43 people, with 63 others missing, and scores displaced, after their homes were destroyed in the deluge. The province's premier Sihle Zikalala, described the situation as the worst catastrophe to befall the province. Several aid organisations have been helping with relief efforts. Sooliman has also commended the community for lending a hand. --ChannelAfrica--